Dr. Billington was a national treasure and this is a great loss to the country. Here are a few photos from when we worked together. He even came up to East Hartford for a visit! pic.twitter.com/cqSqkUwPJX

He was the sage of the nation, the epitome of intellect, grace, and class. He was all that you would want in the Librarian of Congress, the gate keeper of truth and the cumulative knowledge of the nation’s heritage, culture, and literature.

I was deeply saddened to learn of the passing of Dr. James Billington last week. Dr. Billington was the 13th Librarian of Congress @librarycongress. Working with him was like working with a mixture of Gandolf and Dumbledore, because of his knowledge and wisdom.
